[b]Liquidity Hunter [WavesUnchained][/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Liquidity Hunter ranks equal highs and equal lows by quality, detects sweep-and-reclaim events with a composite score, and draws only the two most relevant levels per side. The goal is to reduce chart clutter to the levels that actually matter — those with multiple touches, still fresh, and closest to price.

[b]Liquidity Levels[/b]
[list]
[*]Equal highs (BSL) and equal lows (SSL) are grouped within an ATR-based tolerance
[*]Each cluster is scored by touch count, age, and distance from price
[*]Primary level (solid, thick) and secondary level (dashed) are drawn per side with score and touch labels
[*]Levels too old or too far from price are automatically removed from the registry
[/list]

[b]Level Scoring[/b]
[list]
[*]Touch count drives most of the score — up to 5 touches, 20 points each
[*]Age penalty reduces score as the level's last touch gets older
[*]ATR-distance penalty reduces score as price moves away from the level
[*]Result: levels with many recent touches close to price always rank first
[/list]

[b]Sweep and Reclaim Detection[/b]
[list]
[*]Sweep: wick clears the level by a configurable ATR minimum — marked with an orange triangle
[*]Reclaim: after a sweep, price closes back through the level within a short window — confirmed only with sufficient volume (ratio ≥ 1.2 by default) and close-back depth
[*]Reclaim events are scored separately: wick depth, close-back depth, volume ratio, session boost — capped at 100
[*]Events with score ≥ 65 trigger a Premium alert
[/list]

[b]Bias and Armed Level[/b]
[list]
[*]A bias value is computed from reclaim direction and level proximity — outputs Bullish / Neutral / Bearish
[*]When price is within the alert ATR distance of a primary level, that level is "armed" and the background is highlighted
[*]Dashboard (top-right): bias, primary BSL/SSL price + score + ATR distance, armed state, last event score, recent premium bull/bear scores
[/list]

[b]Stop Hunts and Gaps[/b]
[list]
[*]Stop hunt: same-bar sweep through a known level plus volume spike plus reversal close — labeled HUNT
[*]Unfilled price gaps are drawn as magnet-zone boxes and removed once filled
[/list]

[b]Exhaustion Events (Momentum Hybrid)[/b]
[list]
[*]Built-in WaveTrend qualifies sweeps and stop hunts: a BSL event at a WT extreme above the threshold marks bearish exhaustion, an SSL event below the negative threshold marks bullish exhaustion
[*]Marked with large "EX" triangles; WT state and MFI shown in the dashboard
[/list]

[b]Session Filter[/b]
[list]
[*]Optional — restricts the session boost in reclaim scoring and the bias boost to a defined trading window
[*]Off by default; useful for instruments with clear active sessions (equities, forex majors)
[/list]

[b]Alerts[/b]
[list]
[*]Primary BSL Near / Primary SSL Near
[*]BSL Swept / SSL Swept
[*]BSL Stop Hunt / SSL Stop Hunt
[*]Bearish Reclaim / Bullish Reclaim
[*]Premium Bearish Reclaim / Premium Bullish Reclaim (score ≥ 65)
[*]Exhaustion Bear / Exhaustion Bull
[/list]

